-- 
Boston Red Sox to Make Bobby Valentine New Manager, ESPN Reports

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-11-30T01:32:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/boston-red-sox-to-make-bobby-valentine-new-manager-espn-reports.html
Bobby Valentine accepted an offer to
succeed Terry Francona as manager of the  Boston Red Sox , taking
on one of the most high-profile jobs in Major League Baseball,
 ESPN reported .  Valentine, 61, a baseball analyst for Walt Disney Co.’s
ESPN for the past two seasons, was offered the job today, the
network said, citing an unidentified person close to the team.  Red Sox spokeswoman Pam Ganley said in an e-mail that the
team didn’t have any comment on the ESPN report.  Valentine is the last manager to lead the New York Mets to
the World Series, in 2000, where they lost to the Yankees. He
has 1,117 wins and 1,072 losses in 15 seasons as a major league
manager, including seven years with the Mets and eight with the
 Texas Rangers . He also managed for seven seasons with the Chiba
Lotte Marines in Japan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Gloster in  San Francisco  at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
